Next, you can add more details to your catfish head drawing. Here are some steps you can follow:
1. Add the eyes: Draw two oval shapes for the eyes, and add small circles inside for the pupils.
2. Add the mouth: Draw a curved line below the eyes to represent the mouth. You can also add some small lines to indicate the lips.
3. Add the whiskers: Draw several long, thin lines extending from the sides of the mouth to represent the whiskers. Make sure they are evenly spaced.
4. Add the fins: Draw the pectoral fins on the sides of the head, and the dorsal fin on the top. You can also add the anal fin and the caudal fin at the back.
5. Add the details: You can add scales to the head by drawing small, overlapping curved lines. You can also add some shading to create depth and dimension.
Remember to take your time and practice, and don't be afraid to make adjustments as you go along. Good luck with your catfish head drawing!

2. Prepare the marinade by mixing ingredients like soy sauce, cooking wine, salt, ginger, garlic, and spices.
3. Apply the marinade evenly on the lamb, massaging it into the meat.
4. Let the lamb marinate for at least 2 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.
5. Optionally, wrap the marinated lamb in tin foil before roasting in the oven.
6. Roast the lamb in a preheated oven at 200 degrees Celsius.
7. Flip the lamb halfway through the roasting process and brush with oil or marinating sauce.
8. Continue roasting until the lamb is cooked to your desired doneness.
